  "texts": [
    "Unlearning methods based on local modifications or fine-tuning offer a better balance between speed, unlearning guarantees, and utility of the unlearned models.",
    "All of the surveyed methods in these categories offer approximate guarantees, which in most cases should be sufficient to comply with forgetting requests, especially those related to privacy and copyright issues (dealing with biases and the generation of harmful content is a more complex issue).",
    "These methods can be used to consolidate changes made with the previous approaches without the need to retrain the models.",
    "A more definitive approach to complying with forgetting requests is to retrain the models from scratch, applying any necessary data pre-processing or privacy-preserving training techniques.",
    "Mechanisms such as SISA can also be applied in order to prepare for future unlearning requests."
  ],
